{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01RZythMh7P9QXk9d5Rhu8nv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to generate exactly 10 realistic fake OCR recipe text files. Let me break down the requirements:\n\n1. Save to `tools/title-loop/input/{RECIPE_TITLE}.generated.21.txt`\n2. FILENAME RULES:\n   - Use SPACES, not hyphens/underscores\n   - Preserve Polish diacritics\n   - Title in filename must EXACTLY match main title in content (case-insensitive OK)\n\n3. RECIPE MIX: ~60% English (~6 files), ~40% Polish (~4 files)\n4. Variety: soups, mains, desserts, salads, appetizers, breads, drinks, preserves\n5. Multi-word (2-5 words) and single-word titles\n\n6. AVOID these recipes (there's a long list given)\n\n7. PATTERN REQUIREMENTS for this batch:\n   - 5 files with SIMPLE: basic OCR noise (stray numbers, page headers, broken words)\n   - 3 files with OCR_CORRUPTION: character corruption (digit for letter, dotless i, hyphenation artifacts, garbage tokens)\n   - 2 files with NARRATIVE: 3-7 lines of prose cooking story/intro before ingredient list\n\n8. FILE LENGTH: 15-60 lines. Spillover should be 40-60 lines.\n\nLet me think about 10 recipes I haven't generated yet:\n\nEnglish (6 needed):\n1. Beetroot Risotto - NARRATIVE\n2. Vanilla Panna Cotta - SIMPLE\n3. Harissa Chickpea Salad - OCR_CORRUPTION\n4. Herb Crusted Cod - SIMPLE\n5. Berry Tart with Custard - OCR_CORRUPTION\n6. Roasted Sweet Potato Soup - NARRATIVE\n7. Lemon Basil Pasta - SIMPLE\n8. Fig and Goat Cheese Tart - OCR_CORRUPTION\n\n\n9. Braised Fennel with Tomato - SIMPLE\n10. Spiced Apple Compote - SIMPLE\n\nI need to verify the distribution: 5 SIMPLE, 3 OCR_CORRUPTION, 2 NARRATIVE totals 10. That works. For the English recipes, I have Beetroot Risotto and Roasted Sweet Potato Soup as my two narratives, then five simple files and three corruption files spread across the remaining slots. I need to balance the recipe distribution across languages. I'm aiming for roughly 6 English recipes and 4 Polish ones, with a mix of complexity levels. Let me reorganize: the English section should include the simpler recipes like Vanilla Panna Cotta, Herb Crusted Cod, Lemon Basil Pasta, and Braised Fennel with Tomato, plus Spiced Apple Compote and Roasted Sweet Potato Soup to reach six total. For the Polish recipes, I should create distinct names rather than just translating the English ones, ensuring they're actually Polish dishes instead of duplicating what I've already listed. Compote). Let me reconsider the Polish selections more carefully, checking against what's already been used. I notice Żurawina Kompot is already excluded, so I should pick distinct options instead. Focusing on fresh Polish recipes: Tarta Malinowa works as a narrative entry, Zupa Brukułowa fits the OCR corruption pattern, and Kluski ze Szpinakiem provides a good third option with spinach dumplings.\n\nFor the English recipes, I'm listing six candidates including Vanilla Panna Cotta, Herb Crusted Cod, Lemon Basil Pasta, Braised Fennel with Tomato, Spiced Apple Compote, and Roasted Sweet Potato Soup. Looking at the distribution, I have too many SIMPLE entries at six total—I need to shift one to OCR_CORRUPTION to balance the categories properly, bringing SIMPLE down to five while increasing the corruption category to three.\n\nReassigning Kompot Gruszowy from SIMPLE to OCR_CORRUPTION fixes this. Now the Polish recipes are Tarta Malinowa as NARRATIVE, and Zupa Brukułowa, Kluski ze Szpinakiem, and Kompot Gruszowy all as OCR_CORRUPTION. For the English side, I'll keep Vanilla Panna Cotta and Herb Crusted Cod as SIMPLE entries, each around 15-60 lines with basic OCR artifacts like stray numbers, page headers, and broken words at the margins.\n\nLemon Basil Pasta, Braised Fennel with Tomato, and Spiced Apple Compote follow the same SIMPLE pattern. Roasted Sweet Potato Soup shifts to NARRATIVE with a 3-7 line prose introduction, ingredient list, and 40-60 lines of content. Tarta Malinowa is NARRATIVE in Polish with the same structure. The three remaining Polish recipes—Zupa Brukułowa, Kluski ze Szpinakiem, and Kompot Gruszowy—all feature character-level corruption like 'só1' for 'sól', 'ı' for 'l', hyphenation artifacts, and garbage tokens throughout the Polish text.\n\nNow I'll generate the actual recipe files. For SIMPLE recipes, I'll add page numbers, headers, stray artifacts, broken words at line breaks, and typical OCR noise in ingredient lists. For OCR_CORRUPTION, I'll use digit substitutions (1 for l, 0 for o, 5 for S), dotless ı characters, hyphenation artifacts, and garbage tokens mixed into Polish text. For NARRATIVE recipes, I'll write 3-7 lines of cooking story before the recipe content, extending to 40-60 lines total. Looking at the vanilla panna cotta recipe, I need to work through the preparation steps. The cream gets heated with vanilla bean seeds and pod until steam forms, then allowed to steep briefly. The gelatin blooms in cold water before being stirred into the hot cream mixture until completely dissolved. The mixture is strained and poured into serving vessels, then refrigerated for several hours until set. Optional fresh berries can be added as garnish.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":17233,"cache_read_input_tokens":65286,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":17233},"output_tokens":7,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d9992f69-ad3e-4c1d-a1f9-18c10f385629","uuid":"24249500-f708-4289-9129-5e05dbabd4fa"}
