{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Wtm24roNiGEusAZzTQr2pt","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Vanilla Panna Cotta.generated.21.txt"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d9992f69-ad3e-4c1d-a1f9-18c10f385629","uuid":"ddb735fa-4855-44eb-9992-fec56cf97dba","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Vanilla Panna Cotta.generated.21.txt","content":"DESSERTS & PUDDINGS                    42\n\nVanilla Panna Cotta\n\nIngredients:\n1/2 cup heavy cream\n1/4 cup sugar (granulated)\n1 vanilla bean, split & sc-\n  raped\nPinch of salt\n2 tbsp water\n1 tsp gelatin powder\n\nMethod:\n1. Combine cream and sugar in saucepan\n2. Split vanilla bean and scrape out seeds\n3. Add vanilla seeds and pod to cream\n4. Heat over medium until small steam rises\n5. Remove from heat and let steep 10 min\n6. Sprinkle gelatin over cold water 5 min\n7. Stir gelatin mixture into hot cream until\n   fully dissolved - no lumps!\n8. Strain through fine-mesh sieve to remove\n   pod pieces and ensure smooth texture\n9. Divide into serving ramekins or small bowls\n10. Refrigerate at least 4 hours, preferably\n   overnight for best set\n\nVariations: Add bourbon (1 tsp) or coffee\npowder (1/2 tsp) for flavor variations.\n\nServes 4-6      Prep 15 min     Chill 4+ hrs\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
