{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_013X9ru8aAbRLUeemo2L8K4p","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_015WCWEYVp6rgW2SUx6bTQaD","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Roasted Sweet Potato Soup.generated.21.txt","content":"SOUPS & BROTHS                          234\n\nRoasted Sweet Potato Soup\n\nThere is something deeply comforting about a bowl of velvety sweet\npotato soup, especially as the autumn leaves begin to fall and the\nevenings grow cool. This recipe came to me one October afternoon while\nbrowsing a farmers market laden with plump orange squashes and humble\nroot vegetables. The combination of roasted sweet potatoes with warming\nspices like cumin and cinnamon creates an almost dessert-like dish that\nis paradoxically savory and complex. I found myself ladling bowl after\nbowl, always reaching for one more spoonful, as the flavors seemed to\ndeepen with each sip.\n\nIngredients:\n3 lbs sweet potatoes, peeled & cubed\n3 tablespoons olive oil\n1 large onion, diced 456\n4 cloves garlic, minced\n6 cups vegetable broth\n1/2 cup coconut milk or cream\n1 tablespoon cumin\n1 teaspoon cinnamon\n1/2 teaspoon turmeric\n1/4 teaspoon cayenne pepper\n2 tablespoons maple syrup\n2 tablespoons lime juice\nSalt and pepper to taste\nToasted pumpkin seeds for garnish\nFresh cilantro for garnish\n\nMethod:\n1. Preheat oven to 425°F\n2. Toss sweet potato cubes with 2 tbsp olive\n   oil, salt, and pepper\n3. Spread on baking sheet in single layer\n4. Roast for 30-35 minutes until golden &\n   caramelized at edges\n5. Heat remaining 1 tbsp oil in large pot\n6. Add diced onion and cook until soft, about\n   5 minutes\n7. Add minced garlic and cook 1 minute more\n8. Stir in cumin, cinnamon, turmeric, cayenne\n9. Toast spices for 30 seconds until fragrant\n10. Add roasted sweet potatoes to pot\n11. Pour in vegetable broth\n12. Bring to simmer and cook 10 minutes\n13. Remove from heat and add coconut milk\n14. Blend soup until smooth (use immersion\n    blender or regular blender in batches)\n15. Stir in maple syrup and lime juice\n16. Taste and adjust seasonings\n17. Serve hot, garnished with pumpkin seeds\n    and fresh cilantro\n\nServing variations: Top with crispy sage\nleaves, toasted walnuts, or a drizzle of\nspiced oil. Also excellent served chilled\nin summer as a gazpacho-style starter.\n\nStorage: Keeps refrigerated 4-5 days or can\nbe frozen up to 3 months.\n\nServes 6-8      Prep 20 min     Cook 50 min\n\nPage 234-236\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":521,"cache_read_input_tokens":87502,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":521},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d9992f69-ad3e-4c1d-a1f9-18c10f385629","uuid":"f01ddc1b-34a8-4137-b394-12c98f1c275f"}
